Description


A brand new Japan Made Seiko 5 SNKP21J1 with a special Black Arabic Dial and day/date complication (can be set in English and Arabic).





This famous watch is marvel amongst watch lovers and collectors as it incorporates a beautiful and unique Arabic dial in the Seiko 5 Range.


Among its unique features is the crown which is positioned at 3 o’clock rather than usual 4 o'clock in other seiko 5’s





The watch comes at about 42mm in diameter which is a perfect size for medium to large wrists.





At the heart of the watch is the proven 7S26 calibre which boasts 21 jewels, 40 hours of Power reserve and a respectable 50M water resistance.





The hands and indices illuminate in the dark via the famous seiko Lumibrite.





Unlike the more recent Seiko 5 models which are manufactured in various parts of the world, this particular timepiece is manufactured in Japan.





The watch comes with a box, papers, and 1 year international manufacturer warranty.

ABOUT


This pre-owned 2014 Omega De Ville Chronoscope 422.10.41.50.04.001 is in like new condition. The watch comes as a full set, along with additional 1 year warranty from The Watch Village.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




This incredibly rare De Ville features an impressive chronoscope dial that is packed with an impressive array of watchmaking complications. With the white dial being decorated with gold coloured hands and numeral markers. Surrounding which is a plain bezel, sat upon a 41mm stainless steel case and presented on a matching steel bracelet. All powered by the Omega Co-Axial Calibre 3313 automatic movement.
